The Bible Society of Nigeria, a not-for-profit Christian organisation, is holding the maiden edition of a bible quiz for the deaf on Thursday (today.) The Bible quiz, which will be conducted in the Nigerian sign language, will hold at the Christian Mission for the Deaf, Shomolu, according to a statement by the BSN. The BSN stated that the quiz was being organised in fulfilment of its mission to meet the scriptural needs of every Nigerian, including the deaf, and to help people interact with the Word of God. The BSN, which has a Deaf Translation Centre in Ibadan, Oyo State, has translated the Bible into Nigerian sign language for the deaf from which the contestants are expected to answer questions from 32 out of the 110 chronological bible stories. Copyright PUNCH.
